  "body": "<!-- Briefly describe the issue you're experiencing. Tell us what you were trying to do and what happened instead. -->\r\nincreaseAllowance function in ERC20 expect uint256 value, which has no check on the upper bounds. Although the failure returns a false, there should be an early exit with a descriptive message\r\n\r\n<!-- Remember, this is not a place to ask for help debugging code. For that, we welcome you in the OpenZeppelin Community Forum: https://forum.openzeppelin.com/. -->\r\n\r\n**üíª Environment**\r\n\r\n<!-- Tell us what version of OpenZeppelin Contracts you're using, and how you're using it: Truffle, Remix, etc. -->\r\n**üìù Details**\r\nVersion : latest\r\nIDE : Remix\r\n\r\n<!-- Describe the problem you have been experiencing in more detail. Include as much information as you think is relevant. Keep in mind that transactions can fail for many reasons; context is key here. -->\r\n\r\naddAllowance  function in ERC20 expect uint256 value, which has no check on the upper bounds. Although the failure returns a false, there should be an early exit with a descriptive message\r\n\r\n**üî¢ Code to reproduce bug**\r\n\r\nincreaseAllowance(spender, type(uint).max);\r\n\r\n<!-- We will be able to better help if you provide a minimal example that triggers the bug. -->\r\n",
